Residents of an informal settlement in Shallcross, Durban have been sent a water tanker, after protesting over food parcels and water earlier on Sunday. Courtesy of #DStv403 DURBAN - Residents of an informal settlement in Shallcross, Durban have been sent a water tanker, after protesting over food parcels and water on Sunday. The local councillor has urged residents to apply to Sassa for food parcels. READ: 12 people arrested in Durban for lockdown breaches Residents blocked Link Road in protest; demanding water, which they say they haven’t had in over a week. The residents are also concerned about the risk of contracting COVID-19 without facilities to maintain their hygiene. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.